le></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=ES%2FH043586%2F1"><gtr:id>BD22FCE5-0590-4B9E-B80B-10076EE44BA1</gtr:id><gtr:title>Producing a video to disseminate research on seafarers' fatigue</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Research Grant</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/H043586/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>Around 90 per cent&amp;nbsp;of all goods are transported by ship yet the maritime industry remains largely hidden from public consciousness. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>Seafarers' fatigue is a significant problem currently facing the maritime industry and this project aims to disseminate key research findings in this area using the medium of film. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The Cardiff University Seafarers' Fatigue research programme was conducted over the course of 5 years and involved a range of research methods from performance testing to noise and motion measurement, questionnaires, sleep assessment and cortisol sampling. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>This research was conducted both onboard ship and using remote research methods and represented a significant step forward for the field. The current project aims to disseminate the findings of this research programme using film. As well as 'talking through' academic papers on the subject using diagrams, graphs and tables, the film will also incorporate interviews with seafarers, footage onboard ship and case studies to help bring the subject alive to people unfamiliar with this world. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>Those who watch the film will learn about research methods, psychology and ergonomics in addition to gaining a fuller understanding of the seafaring industry which underpins much of what we take for granted in modern life. &lt;br />&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2011-06-07</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2010-07-08</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>9950</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutput><gtr:description>A research film on fatigue in seafarers.</gtr:description><gtr:id>886F3F6C-2C6B-4B49-95DE-24866C32B0CB</gtr:id><gtr:impact>14,000+ people have currently seen the film on YouTube around the world</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>r-7212623178.2255919c9e1614</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:title>Seafarers fatigue film : Cardiff University</gtr:title><gtr:type>Film/Video/Animation</gtr:type><gtr:yearFirstProvided>2011</gtr:yearFirstProvided></gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutput></gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>Talk at the Institute of Marine Engineering, Science &amp; Technology (IMarEST)</gtr:description><gtr:form>A talk or presentation</gtr:form><gtr:geographicReach>International</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>85F04466-1413-40C9-9C38-135580760DD8</gtr:id><gtr:impact>We were invited to screen the film at the Institute of Marine Engineering, Science &amp;amp; Technology (IMarEST) in Newcastle. A presentation of the research was given before a screening of the film and time for questions.

