lm will reflect negatively on the quality of the research being discussed.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>The use of the film in industry training courses, along with invites to present at maritime events is strong evidence of the use of the film in non-academic contexts. Over 30 feedback comments have been received through the website which give testament to the fact that the largest audience for the film is active seafarers working in the industry. The film is already being used by the industry in four training courses and two fatigue awareness campaigns. Having the film available online also acts as a central resource for anyone interested in the topic. YouTube statistics show the film has been viewed over 20,000 times in over 20 different countries.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>D9BC1C0C-1867-4A36-BED6-D4B73876C6E5</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>r-8236078078.147097b2f29f92</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Aerospace, Defence and Marine,Transport</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors><gtr:url>http://www.seafarersfatigue.com</gtr:url></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>FFD04404-1BFE-4EA0-B2DE-96F64CCFA756</gtr:id><gtr:title>Seafarers' fatigue : the impact of the Cardiff research programme and film</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/6c90c7ed979a0e69e96c41c7631cb020"><gtr:id>6c90c7ed979a0e69e96c41c7631cb020</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>A.P. Smith (Author)</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2012-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>r_7098598087cb160c16</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>DED379A4-9590-4F3A-8B5A-2027DECBC4A0</gtr:id><gtr:title>Using video to disseminate research on seafarers' fatigue</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri